main event: An unidentified object was sighted moving at high speed, reported by Tyndall Radar in 1950.
interesting points: The object was sighted at approximately 2252 EST in the south-southwest and was noted to be moving faster than any jet aircraft., There were multiple tracking reports of objects at different times, indicating a pattern of sightings., A prior report mentioned a possible meteor or constellation for an object that headed out to sea., The incident was part of a broader investigation during Project Blue Book., The report indicates the object was not likely to be a conventional aircraft.
